===Etymology===
From {{compound|en|nil|potent|t1=not any|t2=having power}} with literal meaning “having zero power” - bearing {{etyl|la|en}} roots {{m|la|nil}} and {{m|la|potens}}.
Coined in 1870, along with {{m|en|idempotent}}, by American mathematician {{w|Benjamin Peirce}} to describe elements of [[associative]] [[algebra]]s.

